column1: #Text=Melbourne Beach is a town in Brevard
#Text=Space Coast Area Transit is the name of the local Brevard County bus service .
#Text=It is a cheap way to get around and is handicap accessible .
#Text=Buses travel to most sites and places of interest . $ 1.25 per ride , or $ 35 for a monthly pass .
#Text=Sebastian Inlet State Park , 9700 South A1A ( 15 miles south of Melbourne Beach ) , ☏ +1 321-984-4852 .
#Text=Fishing on the beach , the Indian River Lagoon at Honest John 's Fishing Camp , at Sebastian Inlet State Park or charter a boat with Capt Dick Catri .
#Text=Sea turtle watch tour in Archie Carr National Wildlife Refuge .
#Text=Golf at Spessard Holland public golf course .
#Text=Kayak or canoe at Mullet Creek from historic Honest John 's Fishing Camp .
#Text=Inlet Bait & Tackle , inside the Sebastian Inlet State Park
#Text=Long Point Bait & Tackle , at the entrance to Long Point Park and Campground
#Text=Gold Star Bait & Tackle , on Ocean Ave in downtown Melbourne Beach
#Text=Seafood is the best , caught fresh daily .
#Text=Surfin ' Turtle Bar and Grill , sports bar
#Text=Family owned , excellent upscale restaurant with beautiful view of sunsets on the river .
#Text=Boardwalk Burrito Located among the eateries at the end of US 192 , beside Starbucks and Coldstone Creamery .
#Text=Made to order Burritos , Nachos , Fajitas , etc similar in style to the Moe 's franchise .
#Text=Specials : Tuesday after 4PM-2 for 1 price tacos($ 3.50 , the Mahi Mahi tacos are best ) and Friday after 4PM are half price nachos ( you can get ultimate nachos and a drink for ~$ 6 )
#Text=Friendly Toast ( formerly known as " Friendly Toast " ) , 300 Ocean Ave , ☏ +1 321-733-5590 .
#Text=You can eat inside ( usually crowded ) or at a few tables outside .
#Text=Pride and Joy Environmental Resort , for allergen sensitive .
#Text=Ocean views , private porches , delicious breakfasts , concierge service .
